GEOPlatformSearch

GEOPlatformSearch.Rd

search for GEO platform name updated 08/2020

GEOPlatformSearch(
  x,
  species = NULL,
  file = GEOplatform,
  contain_all = TRUE,
  accession_only = FALSE
)

Arguments

x

a string or character vector to search for. input character vector if searching for multiple terms.
species

species name to narrow down the search. partial input of an organism name is allowed. e.g. results for species "Homo sapiens" will be pulled if input "homo".
file

dataframe for platform infomation. contains "Title" to search for and "Taxnomy" for organism, and "Accession" for platform name. Optional. GEOplatform file will be loaded if not provided.
contain_all

if TRUE, results contain all search terms will be returned. if FALSE, results contain any of the given term will be returned.
accession_only

if TRUE, only accession id of the search will be returned as a character. if FALSE, the complete information of the platforms will be returned as a dataframe.

Value

character or dataframe of search result

Examples

GEOPlatformSearch("illumina")
